On Wed, Dec 22, 2010 at 1:40 PM, James <boletivore(-at-)gmail.com> wrote:
> I am fighting State Farm right now and they say mine is worth $4400 but want
 $1100 to sell it back to me.

That's normal insurance industry practice. It means that you get $4400
for your loss.

Then they have to dispose of it at auction. It means they expect to
get $1100 for it, so they are offering to let you keep it with a
salvage title if you are willing to reduce your $4400 award by $1100.

